{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-1636","published":"2022-05-11T11:03:44Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:18:07.975934Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-24839"],"summary":"nekohtml security update","details":"NekoHTML is a simple HTML scanner and tag balancer that enables application programmers to parse HTML documents and access the information using standard XML interfaces.\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\norg.cyberneko.html is an html parser written in Java. The fork of `org.cyberneko.html` used by Nokogiri (Rubygem) raises a `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError` exception when parsing ill-formed HTML markup. Users are advised to upgrade to `>= 1.9.22.noko2`. Note: The upstream library `org.cyberneko.html` is no longer maintained. Nokogiri uses its own fork of this library located at https://github.com/sparklemotion/nekohtml and this CVE applies only to that fork. Other forks of nekohtml may have a similar vulnerability.(CVE-2022-24839)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"nekohtml","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/nekohtml&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.9.22-9.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"noarch":["nekohtml-1.9.22-9.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["nekohtml-1.9.22-9.oe1.src.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2022-1636.json"}},{"package":{"name":"nekohtml","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/nekohtml&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.9.22-9.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"noarch":["nekohtml-1.9.22-9.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["nekohtml-1.9.22-9.oe1.src.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2022-1636.json"}},{"package":{"name":"nekohtml","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/nekohtml&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":